\title{Beta-reduction}

\p{\strong{#{\beta}-reduction} is a [reduction rule](plt-languages-000F) that allows an
application of a lambda abstraction to be simplified by substituting the argument for the
bound variable in the body of the abstraction. Formally, it is defined as follows: 

##{\frac{\begin{array}{cc}
          (\lambda x.e_1)~e_2 
        \end{array}}
       {e_1[e_2/x]}}
}
